	   <tr><td colspan=2>Gavalt!<br><br>Sorry, I had to say that.&nbsp;&nbsp;A little Yiddish slang is always a welcome addition to a staid board like this one.<br><br>I have to say one thing-- why in the world would you be willing to spend hours making fish goodies for money when you could be out fighting/trading/traveling?  Just for a bit more money to buy something to whack a mob with?  Go out and mingle!  Stuff is just that: stuff.  Other than a weapon which makes killing something marginally easier, the equipment upgrades in EQ are negligible in terms of genuine usefulness.  The items which make a big difference in your character's life are so costly as to prohibative in price.<br><br>If you look at the various stats of all the equipment out there you will see very little difference.  So where does that leave you?  As a monk you will eventually need low weight, but the fist eventually becomes a fantastic weapon with zero weight.  <br><br>I guess what I am trying to say is it really does not make any difference at all what you spend your money on since there is not much difference between all the stuff in the game.  Instead, just go out and enjoy the people and time spent with friends.<br><br>--Pusbag Infection, King of the Trolls<br>&nbsp;<br>Emperor and Shamanic High Priest of the Trolls<br>"Worship Innoruuk, you worthless cattle!"<br></td></tr>
